com.solacesystems.solclientj.core.handle

Interface MessageSupport

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    FlowHandle, MessageDispatchTargetHandle, SessionHandle

    public interface MessageSupport
    The MessageSupport interface provides a common API for handling received messages. Applications do not need to instantiate or extend objects with this interface. This interface is already included in all the solclientj interfaces where it is required:
    • SessionHandle
    • FlowHandle
    • MessageDispatchTargetHandle
    NOTE: These methods are only applicable in the context of a MessageCallback.onMessage()

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      MessageHandle getRxMessage()
      This method returns a MessageHandle reference valid only in the context of the of MessageCallback.onMessage().
      void takeRxMessage(MessageHandle in_out_messageHandle)
      Use this method to make the received message available outside the scope of MessageCallback.onMessage() Note: client applications must call Handle.destroy() on the MessageHandle reference when they are done with it

    • Method Detail

      • getRxMessage

        MessageHandle getRxMessage()
        This method returns a MessageHandle reference valid only in the context of the of MessageCallback.onMessage(). Client applications that require a MessageHandle reference available outside of the scope of the message callback must call MessageSupport.takeRxMessage() instead.

        Note: client applications must not call Handle.destroy() on the returned MessageHandle reference

        Returns:
        MessageHandle
        See Also:
        MessageSupport.takeRxMessage(com.solacesystems.solclientj.core.handle.MessageHandle)

      • takeRxMessage

        void takeRxMessage(MessageHandle in_out_messageHandle)
            throws SolclientException
        Use this method to make the received message available outside the scope of MessageCallback.onMessage() Note: client applications must call Handle.destroy() on the MessageHandle reference when they are done with it
        Parameters:
        in_out_messageHandle - an "unbound" message handle which gets bound to the received CCSMP message object after the method returns
        Throws:
        SolclientException
